[
  {
    "id": "04836a9c-4395-4683-a1e4-278a0009fee1",
    "title": "How to Create a UI/UX Skill for Claude (Anthropic Agent Skills)",
    "slug": "create-uiux-skill-for-claude-anthropic",
    "date": "March 24, 2026",
    "category": "General",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "A well-built UI/UX skill lets Claude consistently follow your design standards and workflow, without you re-explaining your process every time. Think of it as packaging your design “playbook” into a reusable instruction set that Claude can load automatically when a request matches your triggers."
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "This post walks through how to create a practical UI/UX skill from scratch: structure, frontmatter, triggers, instructions, testing, and iteration."
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "1) What “a skill” is (and why it matters)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "An Anthropic skill is a folder that teaches Claude how to handle a repeatable workflow. At minimum, it contains one required file:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "SKILL.md (required): Markdown instructions with YAML frontmatter",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "scripts/ (optional): Python/Bash utilities for validation or generation",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "references/ (optional): extra docs Claude can open only when needed",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "assets/ (optional): templates, sample output, brand tokens, etc.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "The power comes from progressive disclosure:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Frontmatter: always loaded, used for deciding when to use the skill",
        "listType": "number"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "SKILL.md body: loaded only when the skill is relevant",
        "listType": "number"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Bundled references/assets: loaded only if Claude chooses to open them",
        "listType": "number"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "This keeps context light while still giving Claude strong “specialist” behavior."
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "2) Pick 2–3 concrete UI/UX use cases (start small)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Before writing anything, define what the skill should reliably do."
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Here are strong starter use cases for a UI/UX skill:"
      },
      {
        "type": "h3",
        "text": "Use case A: Turn product requirements into a UX flow"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Trigger phrases: “design a flow”, “UX flow”, “user journey”, “happy path”, “edge cases”"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Result: A structured flow, edge cases, states, error handling, and acceptance criteria."
      },
      {
        "type": "h3",
        "text": "Use case B: Accessibility-first UI review"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Trigger phrases: “accessibility audit”, “WCAG”, “contrast”, “focus state”, “keyboard navigation”"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Result: A prioritized issues list + fixes + test checklist."
      },
      {
        "type": "h3",
        "text": "Use case C: Design critique in a consistent format"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Trigger phrases: “critique this design”, “UX feedback”, “review my UI”"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Result: Feedback organized by severity, user impact, and next steps."
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Pick the ones you actually repeat weekly. You can expand later."
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "3) Create the skill folder (follow the rules exactly)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Folder name must be kebab-case (lowercase, hyphens):"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Inside it, create:"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Critical rules:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "File must be named exactly SKILL.md (case-sensitive).",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Skill name must be kebab-case, no spaces, no capitals.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Do not include README.md inside the skill folder.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Do not put XML angle brackets < > in the frontmatter.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Avoid using “claude” or “anthropic” in the skill name (reserved patterns). You can mention them in the body text.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "4) Write strong YAML frontmatter (this controls when it triggers)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Your frontmatter must answer:"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "1) What it does"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "2) When to use it (trigger phrases)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Here’s a good frontmatter for a UI/UX skill:"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Tips:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Be specific. “Helps with design” is too vague.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Include the phrases people actually type.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "To prevent over-triggering, add boundaries in the description (for example: “Do NOT use for branding”).",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "5) Write the SKILL.md body (your UI/UX workflow)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Below the frontmatter, write clear, actionable steps Claude can follow every time."
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Here’s a solid starter template you can copy into SKILL.md:"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "6) Add optional references (make it smarter without bloating it)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "If you have a personal style guide or recurring patterns (like destructive actions, form validation rules, or UI writing guidance), put them into:"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Then in SKILL.md, tell Claude when to consult them, for example:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“If the flow includes deletion, consult references/destructive-actions-pattern.md.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "7) Testing: make sure it triggers and stays consistent"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Create a mini test set (10–20 prompts)."
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Should trigger"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Create a UX flow for deleting an account safely.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Do an accessibility audit of this settings screen.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Write UI specs for a password reset screen with error states.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Should not trigger"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Write a LinkedIn post about design.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“What’s the weather?”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Help me debug Python” (unless your skill is meant to cover it)",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Then iterate:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "If it doesn’t trigger: add clearer trigger phrases to description.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "If it triggers too often: narrow scope and add “Do NOT use when…”.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "8) Distribution tips (so you can reuse it anywhere)"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "For personal use:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Zip the folder and upload it in Claude’s Skills UI (or place it in your local skills directory).",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "For sharing:"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Host the folder in a GitHub repo.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Put human-facing documentation in the repo-level README (not inside the skill folder).",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "Include example prompts and screenshots.",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "Example starter prompts to include"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Turn this PRD into a UX flow with edge cases and acceptance criteria.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Critique this onboarding screen with severity and suggested fixes.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Design an accessible confirmation modal for destructive actions.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "li",
        "text": "“Create a UI spec for a form: labels, validations, error messages, and states.”",
        "listType": "bullet"
      },
      {
        "type": "hr"
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "text": "Closing"
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "text": "Start with one workflow you repeatedly do (like accessibility-first flow design). Write the skill so the output is always structured, testable, accessible, and consistent. Then expand it over time."
      }
    ],
